HEADWORD: Hackberry
<hw>Hack"ber`ry</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧k"b⟦ecr⟧r`r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of trees (<gen>Celtis</gen>) related to
the elm, but bearing drupes with scanty, but often edible, pulp.
<spn>Celtis occidentalis</spn> is common in the Eastern United
States.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hackbolt</ent>⟦br⟧
